load ../subworkflow-lease.maude

--- Coverage: a descendant of the lease holder re-enters the lease its own root
--- holds and runs, rather than blocking.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SUBWORKFLOW-LEASE :
  leaseHeld(r1) wants(r1)
  =>* C:Cfg running(r1) .

--- Coverage: a turn of a different work-unit blocks while the lease is held
--- the cross-work-unit exclusion, recoverable.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SUBWORKFLOW-LEASE :
  leaseHeld(r1) wants(r2)
  =>* C:Cfg blocked(r2) .

--- Coverage: the deadlock sentinel has teeth. Seeded with a same-unit block
--- which the per-turn mis-keying would produce, the deadlock marker is reachable.
--- This proves the bite below is not vacuous from a dead rule.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SUBWORKFLOW-LEASE :
  leaseHeld(r1) blocked(r1)
  =>* C:Cfg deadlock .

--- Bite: the re-entrant lease is deadlock-free. A descendant of the holder never
--- self-deadlocks. The RESIDUAL soup var means a deadlock in any reachable state
--- is a solution, so No solution proves a parent blocking on a same-workspace
--- child cannot deadlock.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SUBWORKFLOW-LEASE :
  leaseHeld(r1) wants(r1)
  =>* deadlock RESIDUAL:Cfg .
